Just adding a quick note on `RetainPtr`: If we have a type `T` and want to use it in `RetainPtr` we can create a sub class of `T` like this which we can then use for this purpose:
```c++
class RetainableT : public T, public RetainCountable, public Heap::Allocatable<RetainableT>
{
    // May need to explicitly inherit `T` constructors (if we want to use them).
    // for which I guess we can use `using T::T;`
};
```
The `RetainCoutable` adds mechanism to track the ref count, and `Heap::Allocatable` adds `Allocate()` and `Free()` methods. Then we should be able to use `RetainPtr<RetainableT>` .

