@fchollet, How about the following two styles?
- A preprocessing is decouple from a model definition (the current): Several users may be confused because ResNet, ResNetV2, and ResNeXt have similar names. However, in my opinion, there will be no problem for users who are familiar with the current style.
- A preprocessing is defined within a model definition (an alternative): It is reasonable because the certain structure with its pre-trained weights must be coupled with specific preprocessing. However, users who use the current styles (`model.predict(preprocess_input(x))`) must be confused if a preprocessing is included in a model definition. Something complimentary such as a user warning needs to be proposed together.

