When manually testing this PR, I discovered that:
- Set the toggle Off (no auto-extract)
- Load a graph (observe nothing was extracted)
- Set the toggle On (observe nodes auto-extracted)

Then,
- Set the toggle Off again (no auto-extract)

Expected: nothing should be extracted
Actual: high degree nodes still extracted, even though the toggle is Off

I think this surprising behavior manifests because each node's `.include` property is not cleared upon changing the toggle. To correct this, could we split it this L179 observer into a new one separate from the rest ('graphHierarchy', 'edgeWidthFunction', ...), which resets each node's `.include` to be unspecified?

Something like:

```ts
@observe('autoExtractNodes')
_onAutoExtractNodesChanged() {
    if (!this.graphHierarchy) return;
    for (const node of Object.values(this.graphHierarchy.getNodeMap())) {
        node.include = tf_graph.InclusionType.UNSPECIFIED;
    }
    this._buildRenderHierarchy(this.graphHierarchy);
  }
```
