The contents of the method (in this case, **post** are wrapped in a `Fn::If` conditional. CFN doesn't recognize that the `uri` field is wrapped in this conditional (creates an "unresolved resource reference" error), so another conditional is needed around that particular section. This is why we need two conditionals for one template block.

```json
"paths": {
            "/": {
              "post": {
                "Fn::If": [
                  "MyCondition", 
                  {
                    "x-amazon-apigateway-integration": {
                      "httpMethod": "POST", 
                      "type": "aws_proxy", 
                      "uri": {
                        "Fn::If": [
                          "MyCondition", 
                          {
                            "Fn::Sub": "arn:aws:apigateway:${AWS::Region}:lambda:path/2015-03-31/functions/${ImplicitApiFunction.Arn}/invocations"
                          }, 
                          {
                            "Ref": "AWS::NoValue"
                          }
                        ]
                      }
                    }, 
                    "responses": {}
                  }, 
                  {
                    "Ref": "AWS::NoValue"
                  }
